<p><b>Theory of mind</b> is the ability to attribute mental states—beliefs, intents, desires, pretending, knowledge, etc.—to oneself and others and to understand that others have beliefs, desires and intentions that are different from one's own.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Theory of mind is different from <a href="/wiki/Philosophy_of_mind" title="Philosophy of mind">philosophy of mind</a>, although there are philosophical approaches to issues raised in discussions of theory of mind.</p>
